      <element xsi:type="archimate:ApplicationService" name="Manage User Interaction" id="id-78068053578a4910ac8c2053c6c48370"/>
      <element xsi:type="archimate:ApplicationService" name="Provide Instruction Set" id="id-8dbb220395a243058e0f8b68bb70701f"/>
      <element xsi:type="archimate:ApplicationService" name="Provide Semantic Definitions" id="id-b1c2f8ad3b5c41eb85db9e5ad90b0a57"/>
      <element xsi:type="archimate:ApplicationService" name="Provide Service Contracts" id="id-90eb99aba3de40f69d4c769ba6307b6d"/>
    </folder>
    <folder name="components" id="id-483edd418793453b969d483c91d89389">
      <element xsi:type="archimate:ApplicationComponent" name="Entoli Model &amp; Config" id="id-5c60a9024f7d4e049cf444841ac667fd"/>
      <element xsi:type="archimate:ApplicationComponent" name="Entoli Coordination" id="id-e91a272da5ec446a9b29435872d6762f"/>
      <element xsi:type="archimate:ApplicationComponent" name="Entoli Execution" id="id-6bb224a49ad745689e8fff12bc46e137">
        <documentation>Application Service: Deliver Traceable Execution Records&#xD;
&#xD;
Definition:&#xD;
Executes prepared execution contexts and produces traceable artifacts and execution records.&#xD;
&#xD;
Exposed Behavior:&#xD;
&#xD;
Execute service contracts via execution file&#xD;
Invoke LLM and external systems&#xD;
Generate artifacts&#xD;
Register execution traces and provenance&#xD;
&#xD;
Constraint:&#xD;
&#xD;
Must not alter contract semantics&#xD;
Must not reinterpret rules&#xD;
Must ensure full traceability</documentation>
      </element>
      <element xsi:type="archimate:ApplicationComponent" name="Entoli Services" id="id-7ca1df8fbfc7435590926b3d73f65ef3"/>
      <element xsi:type="archimate:ApplicationComponent" name="Entoli Studio" id="id-b3e44d6725114de696e460bbb8c39702"/>
      <element xsi:type="archimate:ApplicationComponent" name="Entoli Agents (git workspace)" id="id-655f853a6fc641fd9e84d9812794a0f9"/>
    </folder>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:ApplicationComponent" name="Entoli Canon (git workspace)" id="id-ae9c0d0843ce4a6d9fb2faef5951f1e4"/>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:DataObject" name="Development phase" id="id-18b7abd4c44941fa91015f313a842f0b">
      <documentation>Development phase is a classification axis that describes in which phase of the formation of work a role or intervention takes place. It positions the work in the chain from intention to operationalisation.&#xD;
&#xD;
POSITIONS DEVELOPMENT PHASE&#xD;
- Exploration — open-ended investigation before commitment&#xD;
- Ordering — structuring and prioritising findings or requirements&#xD;
- Recording — formally capturing decisions, models, or specifications&#xD;
- Testing — verifying and validating against criteria&#xD;
- Accountability — reflecting on and accounting for what has been done&#xD;
- Operationalisation — realising, deploying, or integrating the outcome&#xD;
</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:DataObject" name="Source-regime" id="id-4906771e6247482ca99b3edec7d325f6">
      <documentation>Source-regime is the classification axis that specifies, per agent-contract, which source space the agent may use during an execution, and thus how strictly derivation is bounded. The source-regime records the concrete rules for that position: which sources are valid, which are excluded, and whether interpretation or synthesis is permitted.&#xD;
&#xD;
SOURCE REGIME&#xD;
- Input-bound — the agent works from explicitly provided input&#xD;
- Canon-bound — the agent draws from the canonical foundations&#xD;
- Workspace-bound — the agent draws from workspace artefacts&#xD;
- Externally-bound — the agent draws from an external source (web, API)&#xD;
- Exploratory — the agent explores without a fixed source regime</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:DataObject" name="Business Artiffact" id="id-107ef8b5fd9b446a88363d2b824b1325">
      <documentation>A business artifact is a concrete, durable work product that records content, decisions, analyses, or deliverables produced by an Entoli agent within a value stream phase. It represents substantive output — such as a design, plan, report, code file, or specification — and serves as transferable value within the workspace. A business artifact is one of two subtypes of artifact, distinct from a normative artifact in that it conveys substance rather than prescribing rules or norms.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:DataObject" name="Representation" id="id-3dc8f4bf9af34905bc794e8e24e37ec1">
      <documentation># Representation within the Workspace&#xD;
&#xD;
A **representation** is the form in which meaning is recorded, displayed, or exchanged.&#xD;
&#xD;
A representation describes *how* something is expressed — not *what* it means and not *what role* it fulfils in the workspace.&#xD;
&#xD;
It is independent of:&#xD;
- the process phase in which something arises (development phase),&#xD;
- the nature of the semantic intervention (intervention type),&#xD;
- the governance role of the artifact (artifact-function-axis).&#xD;
&#xD;
A representation is an **expression form of meaning**.&#xD;
&#xD;
---&#xD;
&#xD;
## Definition&#xD;
&#xD;
A representation is a concrete expression of an artifact in a specific form, suitable for human or machine processing.&#xD;
&#xD;
The same meaning can exist in multiple representations without the underlying meaning changing.&#xD;
&#xD;
---&#xD;
&#xD;
## Characteristics&#xD;
&#xD;
- Form-bound, not meaning-determining&#xD;
- Can be translated to other representations&#xD;
- Has no normative force of its own&#xD;
- Can be leading or derived (see Derivation Position)&#xD;
- Serves a specific purpose (readability, executability, visualization, processing)&#xD;
&#xD;
---&#xD;
&#xD;
## Typical representation forms&#xD;
&#xD;
- **Text**: Markdown, Plain text, Gherkin, Guideline document&#xD;
- **Diagram**: ArchiMate view, UML diagram, Process diagram, Capability map&#xD;
- **Model data / Code**: JSON, YAML, XML, SQL, Programming language&#xD;
- **Machine representation**: Compiled code, Binary artifacts, Runtime configuration&#xD;
&#xD;
---&#xD;
&#xD;
## Examples&#xD;
&#xD;
| Meaning | Possible representations |&#xD;
|---------|--------------------------|&#xD;
| API contract | OpenAPI (YAML), generated HTML documentation |&#xD;
| Domain model | UML diagram, JSON model, database DDL |&#xD;
| Architecture principle | Markdown document, Wiki page, PDF |&#xD;
| Requirements | Gherkin file, generated test report |&#xD;
&#xD;
In all cases the meaning remains the same while the form differs.&#xD;
&#xD;
---&#xD;
&#xD;
## Relation to other ordering concepts&#xD;
&#xD;
- **Artifact-function-axis** determines what the artifact means in the workspace (normative, structuring, realising, descriptive).&#xD;
- **Intervention Type** describes what a role does with meaning.&#xD;
- **Development phase** describes where in the chain it arises.&#xD;
- **Representation** describes exclusively the form in which it exists.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:DataObject" name="Derivation Position" id="id-b53367de17794d449cc38da23e42092d">
      <documentation>Derivation Position is the classification axis that specifies the positional relationship of a representation to the authoritative source. It records whether a representation is the leading (primary, authoritative) version or a derived (secondary, generated) copy. A leading representation is the source of truth; derived representations are produced from it and must remain consistent with it.&#xD;
&#xD;
POSITIONS DERIVATION POSITION&#xD;
- Leading — the primary, authoritative representation from which others are derived&#xD;
- Derived — a representation produced or generated from the leading representation</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:DataObject" name="Origin Position" id="id-5c78437e18e544fdb678473ecc70c859">
      <documentation>Origin Position is the classification axis that specifies the initiating context of a business artifact — whether it is created from scratch to start a new thread of work, or built on top of an existing artifact. It records whether an artifact is an initiating artifact (starting a new line of work) or a building-on artifact (extending, refining, or transforming prior work).&#xD;
&#xD;
POSITIONS ORIGIN POSITION&#xD;
- Initiating — the artifact originates a new thread of work without a prior artifact of its type as input&#xD;
- Building-on — the artifact is explicitly derived from or extends an existing artifact</documentation>
    </element>
