      </child>
      <documentation># Entoli Execution &amp; Agent Model — Relations and Cardinalities&#xD;
&#xD;
This view defines the **canonical relationships and cardinalities** between core concepts in the Entoli ecosystem.  &#xD;
It supports **traceability, determinism, and contract-driven execution**.&#xD;
&#xD;
---&#xD;
&#xD;
## 1. Value Stream Structure&#xD;
&#xD;
- **Value Stream → Value Stream Phase**  &#xD;
  - *is decomposed into*  &#xD;
  - `1 → 1..n`  &#xD;
  - Each value stream consists of one or more phases  &#xD;
  - Each phase belongs to exactly one value stream  &#xD;
&#xD;
---&#xD;
&#xD;
## 2. Agent Positioning&#xD;
&#xD;
- **Agent → Value Stream Phase**  &#xD;
  - *operates in*  &#xD;
  - `n → 1`  &#xD;
  - Each agent operates in one primary phase  &#xD;
&#xD;
- **Agent → Formation Phase**  &#xD;
  - *is positioned in*  &#xD;
  - `n → 1`  &#xD;
  - Formation phase is a classification attribute  &#xD;
&#xD;
- **Agent → Operation Mode**  &#xD;
  - *operates under*  &#xD;
  - `n → 1`  &#xD;
  - Defines how the agent operates (stable characteristic)  &#xD;
&#xD;
---&#xD;
&#xD;
## 3. Agent and Capabilities&#xD;
&#xD;
- **Agent → Agent Contract**  &#xD;
  - *exposes capabilities via*  &#xD;
  - `1 → 1..n`  &#xD;
  - An agent exposes one or more capabilities  &#xD;
  - Each contract belongs to exactly one agent  &#xD;
&#xD;
---&#xD;
&#xD;
## 4. Capability Definition (Agent Contract)&#xD;
&#xD;
- **Agent Contract → Intervention Type**  &#xD;
  - *defines*  &#xD;
  - `n → 1`  &#xD;
  - Each capability has exactly one intervention type  &#xD;
&#xD;
- **Agent Contract → Source Regime**  &#xD;
  - *applies*  &#xD;
  - `n → 1`  &#xD;
  - Defines how the capability uses sources  &#xD;
&#xD;
- **Agent Contract → Agent Contract Rule**  &#xD;
  - *is constrained by*  &#xD;
  - `1 → 0..n`  &#xD;
  - A contract may have zero or more rules  &#xD;
&#xD;
---&#xD;
&#xD;
## 5. Input and Output Definition&#xD;
&#xD;
- **Agent Contract → Artifact Type (input)**  &#xD;
  - *requires*  &#xD;
  - `1 → 0..n`  &#xD;
  - Input may be optional  &#xD;
&#xD;
- **Agent Contract → Artifact Type (output)**  &#xD;
  - *produces*  &#xD;
  - `1 → 1..n`  &#xD;
  - Each capability must produce at least one artifact  &#xD;
&#xD;
---&#xD;
&#xD;
## 6. Execution Layer&#xD;
&#xD;
- **Execution → Agent Contract**  &#xD;
  - *executes*  &#xD;
  - `n → 1`  &#xD;
  - Each execution is an instance of one contract  &#xD;
&#xD;
- **Orchestration Run → Execution**  &#xD;
  - *consists of*  &#xD;
  - `1 → 1..n`  &#xD;
  - A run groups one or more executions  &#xD;
&#xD;
---&#xD;
&#xD;
## 7. LLM Interaction&#xD;
&#xD;
- **Execution → LLM Call**  &#xD;
  - *invokes*  &#xD;
  - `1 → 0..n`  &#xD;
  - An execution may result in multiple LLM calls  &#xD;
&#xD;
---&#xD;
&#xD;
## 8. Artifact Flow&#xD;
&#xD;
- **Execution → Artifact (produces)**  &#xD;
  - *produces*  &#xD;
  - `1 → 1..n`  &#xD;
  - Each execution produces one or more artifacts  &#xD;
&#xD;
- **Execution ↔ Artifact (consumes)**  &#xD;
  - *consumes*  &#xD;
  - `n ↔ n`  &#xD;
  - Executions may consume multiple artifacts  &#xD;
  - Artifacts may be reused across executions  &#xD;
&#xD;
---&#xD;
&#xD;
## 9. Artifact Typing&#xD;
&#xD;
- **Artifact → Artifact Type**  &#xD;
  - *is of type*  &#xD;
  - `n → 1`  &#xD;
  - Each artifact has exactly one type  &#xD;
&#xD;
## 10. Doctrine Binding&#xD;
&#xD;
- **Agent Contract Rule → Doctrine Rule**  &#xD;
  - *derives from*  &#xD;
  - `n → 1`  &#xD;
  - Each agent contract rule is a contextual binding of exactly one doctrine rule  &#xD;
  - A doctrine rule may be bound to zero or many agent contracts via agent contract rules  &#xD;
&#xD;
---&#xD;
&#xD;
## 11. Key Design Constraints&#xD;
&#xD;
- **Intervention Type is defined at capability level (Agent Contract), not Agent level**&#xD;
- **Source Regime is defined per capability**&#xD;
- **Execution is strictly bound to one contract**&#xD;
- **Produced and consumed artifacts are distinct relations**&#xD;
- **Determinism is enforced through one-to-many and many-to-one constraints (avoid uncontrolled many-to-many)**&#xD;
&#xD;
---&#xD;
&#xD;
## 11. Architectural Principle&#xD;
&#xD;
> **Agents provide capabilities, contracts define behavior, coordination prepares execution, and execution produces traceable artifacts.**&#xD;
&#xD;
Agent Contract Rules are contextual bindings that derive from canonical Doctrine Rules and constrain the behavior of specific capabilities.</documentation>
    </element>
